WEBVTT

00:00.875 --> 00:02.627
Previously on
"Superman & Lois"...

00:02.627 --> 00:03.920
- Crime's up.
- So are profits.

00:03.920 --> 00:05.547
Well, where's
that money going?

00:05.547 --> 00:08.091
Straight to Lex
and his people in Metropolis.

00:08.091 --> 00:09.509
What, you want to take
Luthor out?

00:09.509 --> 00:11.761
What the hell is wrong
with you?

00:11.761 --> 00:12.387
I know your family.

00:12.387 --> 00:15.306
And not just that sister
of yours in Metropolis.

00:15.306 --> 00:16.725
Where is Darlene?

00:16.725 --> 00:18.810
Anything happens to me,
they all die.

00:18.810 --> 00:21.396
Isn't risking a few lives

00:21.396 --> 00:23.857
for a breakthrough that could
save millions worth it?

00:23.857 --> 00:25.567
But jeopardizing
even one life--

00:25.567 --> 00:27.027
This is your wife
we're talking about!

00:27.027 --> 00:28.737
I'm not sure that it is.

00:28.737 --> 00:30.196
I don't want to just be
cancer friends, though.

00:30.196 --> 00:31.573
I want to be friend friends.

00:31.573 --> 00:32.782
This isn't really the recipe

00:32.782 --> 00:34.784
for a lifelong friendship.

00:34.784 --> 00:36.870
My husband's not
who you think he is.

00:36.870 --> 00:39.998
Everything he's done,
it's all been for me.

00:42.292 --> 00:45.253
[heart beating]

00:45.253 --> 00:48.256
[melancholy music]

00:48.256 --> 00:55.388
♪ ♪

01:47.232 --> 01:54.239
♪ ♪

02:42.912 --> 02:44.247
Oh, that's all
you're gonna eat?

02:44.247 --> 02:46.166
I'll grab a bite
at the station.

02:46.166 --> 02:48.626
Mr. Cushing wants me to show up
a little early for my shift.

02:48.626 --> 02:50.170
Your shift?

02:50.170 --> 02:52.213
Dude, you're a trainee,
not a firefighter.

02:52.213 --> 02:55.008
Whatever, man.

02:55.008 --> 02:56.759
Speaking of training,
I'm not sure I can make it

02:56.759 --> 02:58.678
- to the fortress today.
- That's okay; I actually had

02:58.678 --> 03:00.680
a plan to hang out
with Sarah later, anyway.

03:00.680 --> 03:01.890
Oh, just you and Sarah?

03:01.890 --> 03:04.017
As friends. It can be done.

03:04.017 --> 03:05.768
I mean, look at you
and Ms. Lang.

03:05.768 --> 03:07.353
Yeah.

03:07.353 --> 03:09.731
[phone dings]

03:14.152 --> 03:17.197
[soft music]

03:17.197 --> 03:24.329
♪ ♪

03:26.289 --> 03:28.041
[door clicks]

03:28.041 --> 03:32.879
Okay, I got
three cappuccinos, a latte...

03:32.879 --> 03:35.340
[clears throat]

03:35.340 --> 03:38.968
Am I...late or something?

03:38.968 --> 03:40.887
You think 'cause you got
a shirt with your name on it,

03:40.887 --> 03:43.264
you're the big cheese
of Smallville now?

03:43.264 --> 03:44.849
We don't just let anyone
off the streets

03:44.849 --> 03:46.935
join this station, son.

03:46.935 --> 03:49.312
Yes, sir. I know that.

03:49.312 --> 03:51.856
And if we're gonna invest
the time it takes to train you,

03:51.856 --> 03:53.441
you gotta promise us
you understand

03:53.441 --> 03:55.068
the commitment you're making

03:55.068 --> 03:56.903
and that you're gonna
give us your all.

03:56.903 --> 03:58.321
And that no matter
how hard it gets,

03:58.321 --> 04:00.865
you are not gonna give up.

04:00.865 --> 04:03.117
I promise
I'm not gonna give up.

04:03.117 --> 04:06.120
[tense music]

04:06.120 --> 04:07.664
♪ ♪

04:07.664 --> 04:10.083
We know.

04:10.083 --> 04:13.336
[cheers and applause]

04:13.336 --> 04:16.339
[soft music]

04:16.339 --> 04:19.926
♪ ♪

04:19.926 --> 04:21.386
You are now officially a member

04:21.386 --> 04:24.013
of the National Junior
Firefighter Program.

04:24.013 --> 04:25.348
Wait, seriously?

04:25.348 --> 04:28.434
You ready to do this
for real?

04:28.434 --> 04:30.144
Absolutely.

04:30.144 --> 04:31.938
Well, then I think it's time
we show little Kent here

04:31.938 --> 04:33.481
how to throw a ladder.

04:33.481 --> 04:35.233
[laughter]

04:37.944 --> 04:41.364
[applause]

04:41.364 --> 04:47.120
♪ ♪

04:47.120 --> 04:49.163
God, Mom.
Do you ever stop working?

04:49.163 --> 04:52.792
Oh, you wouldn't believe
how many emails I get a day.

04:52.792 --> 04:54.836
[phone chimes]

04:54.836 --> 04:57.797
[sighs]

04:57.797 --> 05:00.008
- Is everything okay?
- Yeah.

05:00.008 --> 05:01.759
It's just a reminder
of a concert

05:01.759 --> 05:04.971
I was supposed to go to
with your father.

05:04.971 --> 05:07.390
Oh.

05:07.390 --> 05:08.850
Cool.

05:08.850 --> 05:11.894
- So who's playing?
- The Cure.

05:11.894 --> 05:14.981
- I'm not really that familiar.
- [chuckles]

05:14.981 --> 05:17.525
Every time I hear
"Just Like Heaven,"

05:17.525 --> 05:19.610
it takes me right back
to high school.

05:19.610 --> 05:23.156
Is that supposed
to be a good thing?

05:23.156 --> 05:25.241
Wait, why don't
you come with me?

05:25.241 --> 05:27.035
It could be so fun.

05:27.035 --> 05:30.038
Kind of like a girls' night out
in Metropolis.

05:30.038 --> 05:31.664
Yeah. It--it seems nice.

05:31.664 --> 05:34.834
It's just, I don't
really know their music.

05:34.834 --> 05:36.753
Then I'll make you a mix CD.

05:36.753 --> 05:38.921
[snorts] Mom, I--

05:38.921 --> 05:41.549
I don't have a CD player,
and it would just be

05:41.549 --> 05:43.092
a really expensive waste
of a ticket.

05:43.092 --> 05:45.511
Yeah.

05:45.511 --> 05:48.222
All right.
Well, I'll ask someone else.

05:50.266 --> 05:53.227
Okay.

05:53.227 --> 05:56.356
[coughing]

05:59.734 --> 06:01.277
I'll tell Matteo
we're canceling.

06:01.277 --> 06:02.737
- We're not canceling.
- Peia--

06:02.737 --> 06:04.197
No. I said no.

06:04.197 --> 06:05.615
[sighs]

06:05.615 --> 06:08.201
This is important for our son,

06:08.201 --> 06:09.619
and it's important to me.

06:09.619 --> 06:11.245
You'll have
more opportunities

06:11.245 --> 06:13.498
to meet this girlfriend of his.

06:13.498 --> 06:15.458
I'm meeting her today.

06:15.458 --> 06:17.168
I heard coughing.

06:17.168 --> 06:18.753
You okay, Mom?

06:18.753 --> 06:21.631
Some tea went down
the wrong pipe, is all.

06:23.508 --> 06:28.638
Baby, I got you
a little something for today.

06:31.099 --> 06:34.685
Oh. Okay.

06:34.685 --> 06:36.604
Oh, Mom.

06:36.604 --> 06:38.648
Mom, you didn't
have to do this.

06:38.648 --> 06:40.858
Yeah, I did.

06:40.858 --> 06:43.986
You're gonna look
so handsome in this.

06:46.155 --> 06:47.740
Are you gonna be
crying all day?

06:47.740 --> 06:48.991
[tearfully]
Yeah, probably.

06:48.991 --> 06:52.328
[both laugh]

06:52.328 --> 06:54.664
Come here.

06:54.664 --> 06:57.041
I love it. Thank you.

06:57.041 --> 06:58.751
I love you.

06:58.751 --> 07:00.336
Mwah.

07:00.336 --> 07:02.422
So, um...
[laughs]

07:02.422 --> 07:03.673
How do you get this thing on?

07:03.673 --> 07:05.466
'Cause I--
[both laugh]

07:05.466 --> 07:08.761
- Come on, I'll show you.
- All right.

07:08.761 --> 07:11.431
Bruno Mannheim
should be worried.

07:11.431 --> 07:13.182
He's managed to keep
his marriage a secret.

07:13.182 --> 07:15.393
Why is that?

07:15.393 --> 07:18.729
My guess is, he wants to keep
his private life private.

07:18.729 --> 07:20.440
Except Bruno's
not a private guy.

07:20.440 --> 07:23.234
He's been the public face
of Hob's Bay for years.

07:23.234 --> 07:24.819
There has to be a reason.

07:24.819 --> 07:26.988
No, I think that Bruno knows

07:26.988 --> 07:28.823
this information could lead
to more secrets

07:28.823 --> 07:30.116
he'd rather keep hidden.

07:30.116 --> 07:32.034
That's a bit of a stretch.

07:32.034 --> 07:33.536
Well, actually,
it's a strategy

07:33.536 --> 07:35.163
you gave in your MasterClass.

07:35.163 --> 07:37.957
I never should have done
that stupid series.

07:37.957 --> 07:40.710
Why are you making me feel
like I'm doing something wrong?

07:40.710 --> 07:42.253
We've been working
on this story for months.

07:42.253 --> 07:44.547
Not this story.

07:44.547 --> 07:46.382
Lois, I think
Chrissy is right.

07:46.382 --> 07:48.176
We all agree
Bruno should be in prison.

07:48.176 --> 07:50.595
- And if this could help us--
- I'm just not comfortable

07:50.595 --> 07:52.597
informing the world
about their personal life.

07:52.597 --> 07:54.474
The "Gazette" isn't
a gossip rag.

07:54.474 --> 07:57.268
- This isn't gossip, Lois.
- It reads like gossip to me.

07:57.268 --> 07:58.978
This is news
that our readers want to see.

07:58.978 --> 08:00.229
We're not running it.

08:00.229 --> 08:02.940
[tense music]

08:02.940 --> 08:05.485
I am co-owner of this paper,

08:05.485 --> 08:09.322
and I don't want my name
on this story.

08:10.948 --> 08:12.325
I need to rest.

08:12.325 --> 08:17.497
♪ ♪

08:17.497 --> 08:19.248
I'll talk to her.

08:27.715 --> 08:31.135
I'm so tired of feeling cold
all the time.

08:31.135 --> 08:33.513
Could you please make me
a hot tea, babe?

08:33.513 --> 08:37.225
Yeah, of course.

08:37.225 --> 08:39.977
Look, babe.
[sighs]

08:41.771 --> 08:44.690
Chrissy worked really hard
on that article.

08:47.318 --> 08:48.945
I just don't think
it's appropriate

08:48.945 --> 08:51.989
to out Peia and Bruno's
relationship right now.

08:51.989 --> 08:53.658
I know
the timing isn't great, but--

08:53.658 --> 08:55.368
She has cancer.

08:55.368 --> 08:58.079
She is fighting to survive,
just like I am.

08:58.079 --> 08:59.914
Okay.
So then this is personal.

09:02.500 --> 09:05.211
Yeah. Maybe a little.

09:05.211 --> 09:08.506
But ultimately,
what does that even accomplish?

09:08.506 --> 09:12.009
Bruno being married to Peia
doesn't help us take him down.

09:12.009 --> 09:13.719
I know. It's a tough call.

09:13.719 --> 09:15.096
But you never know

09:15.096 --> 09:16.389
what other secrets
this might shake loose.

09:16.389 --> 09:17.723
I mean, if people looked
closer at us--

09:17.723 --> 09:19.433
They're not us.

09:19.433 --> 09:21.435
But if they looked closer,
they might find out about me,

09:21.435 --> 09:22.478
about Jordan's powers.

09:22.478 --> 09:24.146
Exactly.

09:24.146 --> 09:25.856
That would ruin our lives.

09:25.856 --> 09:27.233
I don't want to do that to her.

09:27.233 --> 09:29.151
But like you said,
they aren't us.

09:29.151 --> 09:31.195
[soft tense music]

09:31.195 --> 09:33.990
Bruno is responsible for
the deaths of a lot of people.

09:33.990 --> 09:35.825
He's almost had me killed.

09:35.825 --> 09:38.286
And one of his guys shot Jordan
in the chest, point blank.

09:40.538 --> 09:42.123
He's the leader of Intergang

09:42.123 --> 09:46.752
and the biggest illegal weapons
dealer in the country.

09:46.752 --> 09:48.170
He's not a good guy, Lois.

09:48.170 --> 09:49.964
- And if Peia married him--
- What?

09:49.964 --> 09:51.591
That means
she can't be good either?

09:51.591 --> 09:54.468
No, but it does mean
their secrets might be

09:54.468 --> 09:57.346
a lot more dangerous than ours.

09:57.346 --> 09:58.848
So it's our job,

09:58.848 --> 10:00.224
our responsibility
as journalists,

10:00.224 --> 10:02.393
to keep digging.

10:02.393 --> 10:05.730
Fine. Fine.

10:05.730 --> 10:07.231
You can look into her,
but you and Chrissy

10:07.231 --> 10:08.608
can do it without me.

10:08.608 --> 10:12.069
I'm done
with the Mannheim stuff.

10:12.069 --> 10:13.112
Okay.

10:13.112 --> 10:17.950
♪ ♪

10:17.950 --> 10:20.202
Can I please have my tea?

10:20.202 --> 10:21.579
Yeah.

10:24.206 --> 10:27.293
[distant sirens wailing]

10:34.592 --> 10:36.260
This is close enough.

10:36.260 --> 10:39.388
[sighs]

10:39.388 --> 10:41.265
You sure you don't need me
to join you?

10:41.265 --> 10:43.434
Dad, I thought you had
someone you need to see.

10:43.434 --> 10:44.560
I do.

10:44.560 --> 10:46.312
But I'm here if you need me.

10:48.981 --> 10:51.651
They're gonna love you.

10:51.651 --> 10:53.277
Thanks, Dad.

10:53.277 --> 10:56.280
[soft music]

10:56.280 --> 11:03.412
♪ ♪

11:07.333 --> 11:10.670
Welcome to Little Ace's.

11:10.670 --> 11:12.171
There she is.

11:12.171 --> 11:15.341
[sweet music]

11:15.341 --> 11:18.719
One second.

11:18.719 --> 11:20.763
- You look amazing.
- Thanks.

11:20.763 --> 11:22.348
I love this bow tie.

11:22.348 --> 11:25.476
Thank you.
It was actually my mom's touch.

11:27.061 --> 11:29.689
Well, come on.
They can't wait to meet you.

11:31.649 --> 11:35.695
Mom, Dad, this is Natalie.

11:35.695 --> 11:37.822
It is so nice
to finally meet you.

11:37.822 --> 11:40.449
Matteo's been talking
about you pretty much nonstop.

11:40.449 --> 11:41.492
- [laughs]
- Mom.

11:41.492 --> 11:43.619
Oh, please. It's nice.

11:43.619 --> 11:45.705
You came all the way
from Smallville?

11:45.705 --> 11:47.790
Yes, sir. Have you been?

11:47.790 --> 11:49.125
Oh, not personally.

11:49.125 --> 11:53.045
But it has been
on my radar lately.

11:53.045 --> 11:54.547
Shall we?

11:54.547 --> 11:56.674
Yeah.

11:59.218 --> 12:00.678
This is a total disaster.

12:00.678 --> 12:03.055
That was basically
our whole front page.

12:03.055 --> 12:04.724
And, I mean,
I'm not gonna publish it

12:04.724 --> 12:07.017
if she's not gonna be
a part of it.

12:07.017 --> 12:08.936
It's a really big story.

12:08.936 --> 12:10.563
I know. I know.

12:10.563 --> 12:13.482
Just give her a day or two
to change her mind.

12:13.482 --> 12:17.111
Great, so we'll just keep
publishing town hall stories

12:17.111 --> 12:19.572
until we can be
real journalists again.

12:19.572 --> 12:20.906
[bell chimes]

12:20.906 --> 12:22.783
- Hey, guys.
- Hey.

12:22.783 --> 12:24.660
Clark, I saw
your truck outside,

12:24.660 --> 12:28.664
and I thought I'd see
if you maybe wanted my tickets

12:28.664 --> 12:30.082
to the Cure tomorrow night?

12:30.082 --> 12:31.459
Oh!

12:31.459 --> 12:33.252
That would be so awesome.

12:33.252 --> 12:36.005
Um, but Lois isn't
feeling great,

12:36.005 --> 12:38.799
and I'm gonna stay in
and take care of her.

12:38.799 --> 12:41.260
Any chance you want them?

12:41.260 --> 12:43.304
I know Kyle's a fan.

12:43.304 --> 12:45.890
Oh. Um, thanks, but no.

12:45.890 --> 12:47.516
I have a conflict.

12:47.516 --> 12:49.935
Not of interest! Oh, my God.

12:49.935 --> 12:53.731
No, I mean, we're--
we're totally, totally cool.

12:53.731 --> 12:55.733
Um, it's just
a conflict of time.

12:55.733 --> 12:58.402
Just timing.

12:58.402 --> 12:59.987
Okay.

12:59.987 --> 13:03.032
Uh, let Lois know
that I'm thinking of her.

13:03.032 --> 13:06.869
- I will.
- Okay.

13:06.869 --> 13:08.537
- [bell chimes]
- Wha--

13:09.705 --> 13:11.415
Was that as awkward as it felt?

13:11.415 --> 13:13.459
I mean, I wasn't even using
the super stuff,

13:13.459 --> 13:15.002
and I could hear
your heartbeat, so--

13:15.002 --> 13:17.213
No!

13:17.213 --> 13:20.591
Look, I think we should
dig deeper into Peia.

13:20.591 --> 13:22.259
Aww, it seems like
someone else has been

13:22.259 --> 13:23.594
taking Lois's MasterClass.

13:23.594 --> 13:25.054
Yeah, I had a front row seat.

13:25.054 --> 13:26.555
Come on.
Let's go to Metropolis.

13:26.555 --> 13:27.723
There's someone there
we should talk to.

13:27.723 --> 13:28.724
Okay.

13:28.724 --> 13:31.393
[gasps] Wait.

13:31.393 --> 13:33.062
Does that mean we're gonna fly?

13:34.980 --> 13:36.524
[yelps]

13:37.942 --> 13:41.070
Now that's flying
done right.

13:41.070 --> 13:43.364
Fly higher. Fly better.

13:43.364 --> 13:47.159
Fly Luthor.

13:47.159 --> 13:50.371
Even in prison,
he's still making money.

13:50.371 --> 13:54.333
Special delivery,
straight from the ARGUS vaults.

13:54.333 --> 13:57.711
Anything and everything
they have on Bruno Mannheim,

13:57.711 --> 13:59.338
even the classified stuff.

13:59.338 --> 14:00.631
Great.

14:00.631 --> 14:02.049
You should take that
to the "Gazette."

14:02.049 --> 14:03.634
Maybe Chrissy and Clark
will find something.

14:03.634 --> 14:04.802
But you've been
on me for months

14:04.802 --> 14:06.136
to get these from Diggle.

14:06.136 --> 14:08.430
- Things have changed.
- Why?

14:08.430 --> 14:09.682
'Cause you've been
getting treatments

14:09.682 --> 14:11.058
at Bruno's hospital?

14:11.058 --> 14:12.768
That doesn't mean
he isn't a criminal.

14:12.768 --> 14:15.437
You've been after this guy
for years.

14:15.437 --> 14:16.605
Doesn't feel right anymore.

14:16.605 --> 14:18.524
"Feel right"?

14:18.524 --> 14:20.150
Is this you talking
or the cancer?

14:20.150 --> 14:22.194
- Dad.
- 'Cause it sounds to me like

14:22.194 --> 14:24.154
you're letting this disease
cloud your judgment.

14:24.154 --> 14:27.449
You're starting
to sound like Clark.

14:27.449 --> 14:29.869
For once, I agree with him.

14:29.869 --> 14:33.163
[solemn music]

14:33.163 --> 14:37.042
You really expect me to believe
Lois Lane isn't one bit curious

14:37.042 --> 14:38.627
about what's in these files?

14:38.627 --> 14:44.466
♪ ♪

14:44.466 --> 14:46.677
Come on, pumpkin.

14:46.677 --> 14:49.763
How about you and I
take a look?

14:49.763 --> 14:52.766
[alarms blaring]
[urgent chatter]

14:52.766 --> 14:54.476
[tense music]

14:54.476 --> 14:56.812
All right, we gotta move!

14:56.812 --> 14:58.355
Fire out at Fowe's. Let's go!

14:58.355 --> 15:02.067
Uh, Mr. Cushing, can I come?

15:02.067 --> 15:04.236
As long as you promise
to stay by the truck.

15:04.236 --> 15:05.946
Watch and observe only.

15:05.946 --> 15:08.157
Let's go! Let's roll.

15:08.157 --> 15:15.289
♪ ♪

15:17.416 --> 15:19.668
[sirens wailing]

15:19.668 --> 15:22.671
[indistinct radio chatter]

15:22.671 --> 15:27.009
♪ ♪

15:27.009 --> 15:30.137
[indistinct shouting]

15:38.896 --> 15:41.398
We're missing one employee.
You got eyes on him, Tamera?

15:41.398 --> 15:43.609
Negative.
All aisles are clear.

15:43.609 --> 15:45.444
[whooshing]

15:45.444 --> 15:47.780
[glass shatters]

15:47.780 --> 15:51.116
[suspenseful music]

15:51.116 --> 15:54.662
[air hissing]

15:54.662 --> 15:57.331
[explosion]

15:59.458 --> 16:02.252
[whooshing]

16:02.252 --> 16:05.881
♪ ♪

16:05.881 --> 16:07.216
I think he inhaled
too much smoke.

16:07.216 --> 16:12.554
♪ ♪

16:12.554 --> 16:14.682
What the hell
are you doing, Kent?

16:16.517 --> 16:18.978
Move.

16:18.978 --> 16:21.313
I told you
to stay by the truck.

16:30.906 --> 16:32.282
What'd I tell you
about staying in the truck?

16:32.282 --> 16:34.118
I just wanted to help.

16:34.118 --> 16:35.494
What, by busting down
the door of a burning building?

16:35.494 --> 16:36.912
No, I didn't--it wasn't--

16:36.912 --> 16:39.081
So you're just gonna
lie to me now?

16:39.081 --> 16:40.457
Look, I know you want
to be a hero, son,

16:40.457 --> 16:41.750
but fires are deadly, okay?

16:41.750 --> 16:44.628
Okay. I'm sorry. I just--

16:44.628 --> 16:47.756
You were a liability today,
and I can't have that.

16:47.756 --> 16:49.842
Does this mean I'm fired?

16:49.842 --> 16:52.386
Hey, Chief, you need to come
and take a look at something.

16:52.386 --> 16:54.388
[tense music]

16:54.388 --> 16:57.808
We'll talk about this later,
but you're done for the day.

16:57.808 --> 17:00.310
Get on home.

17:00.310 --> 17:02.855
Copy. On my way.

17:05.816 --> 17:06.942
I can't believe it.

17:06.942 --> 17:08.861
There is so much here.

17:08.861 --> 17:12.197
I could have used
these files years ago.

17:12.197 --> 17:13.490
What?

17:13.490 --> 17:14.616
It just makes me happy

17:14.616 --> 17:15.784
to see you like this, pumpkin.

17:15.784 --> 17:16.952
Like what?

17:16.952 --> 17:18.871
Like yourself again.

17:20.205 --> 17:22.291
Some of these files
are from weeks

17:22.291 --> 17:24.084
after Lex Luthor killed
Boss Moxie.

17:24.084 --> 17:26.879
It is amazing how quickly
Bruno rose to power.

17:26.879 --> 17:28.630
[phone chimes, buzzes]

17:28.630 --> 17:31.675
Well, he knew how to take
advantage of the chaos.

17:31.675 --> 17:34.011
That's the way
the crime world works.

17:35.345 --> 17:37.222
Oh.

17:37.222 --> 17:39.016
- Who was that?
- No one.

17:39.016 --> 17:41.727
Which means
it was clearly someone.

17:41.727 --> 17:44.813
It's just a reminder
for this...

17:44.813 --> 17:47.483
Senior Swipe meetup thing.

17:48.734 --> 17:50.486
You have a date?

17:50.486 --> 17:52.696
It's coffee at Vicky May's.

17:52.696 --> 17:54.656
Dad, that's a date!

17:54.656 --> 17:55.991
When is it? Tonight?

17:55.991 --> 17:57.034
You have to go.

17:57.034 --> 17:58.368
I can't go now.

17:58.368 --> 17:59.787
We're about to make
a break in the case.

17:59.787 --> 18:02.122
We literally just started.

18:02.122 --> 18:05.834
All the more reason
I should stay and help.

18:05.834 --> 18:08.212
Dad, I've got this.

18:08.212 --> 18:09.588
Besides, it makes me happy

18:09.588 --> 18:11.423
to see you
getting back out there.

18:11.423 --> 18:14.093
So please, get back out there.

18:14.093 --> 18:16.303
[soft music]

18:16.303 --> 18:17.721
For me.

18:17.721 --> 18:20.265
♪ ♪

18:20.265 --> 18:24.186
I've known Peia
for a long time.

18:24.186 --> 18:27.064
She's always been
the sweetest girl.

18:27.064 --> 18:30.067
She used to babysit my daughter
when she was young,

18:30.067 --> 18:33.862
and Diana just loved her.

18:33.862 --> 18:35.489
[laughs]

18:35.489 --> 18:39.243
She always wanted to be
just like Peia.

18:39.243 --> 18:40.702
[both laugh]

18:40.702 --> 18:42.037
It sounds like she was
a good kid.

18:42.037 --> 18:43.372
Yeah.

18:43.372 --> 18:44.581
Would you say she had

18:44.581 --> 18:47.626
any less desirable qualities?

18:47.626 --> 18:49.294
We're just trying
to get a really

18:49.294 --> 18:52.506
full picture of her history.

18:52.506 --> 18:54.383
Hmm.

18:54.383 --> 18:59.054
Well, back when
she was in high school...

18:59.054 --> 19:02.516
[sighs]

19:02.516 --> 19:06.353
I don't know, it was like...

19:06.353 --> 19:07.980
something happened to her.

19:07.980 --> 19:10.315
What do you mean?

19:10.315 --> 19:15.195
She became quiet
and withdrawn.

19:15.195 --> 19:19.158
I never saw her smile or laugh.

19:19.158 --> 19:21.577
Any idea
what might have happened?

19:23.745 --> 19:26.832
It wasn't my place to pry.

19:26.832 --> 19:31.461
But when she married Bruno,
it was wonderful.

19:31.461 --> 19:35.883
It was like Bruno taught Peia

19:35.883 --> 19:38.385
how to find her voice again.

19:38.385 --> 19:41.346
That man reminded her
how to smile.

19:41.346 --> 19:43.515
So random question:

19:43.515 --> 19:45.350
do you think that Peia had
any knowledge

19:45.350 --> 19:47.477
of Bruno's ties to Intergang?

19:47.477 --> 19:50.022
[soft tense music]

19:50.022 --> 19:53.483
Exactly what kind of article
are you writing?

19:53.483 --> 19:56.236
Peia has nothing in her heart
but kindness

19:56.236 --> 20:00.199
for the people
of this community.

20:00.199 --> 20:03.076
You should know that by now.

20:03.076 --> 20:04.661
Shame on you.

20:04.661 --> 20:08.332
♪ ♪

20:12.878 --> 20:16.089
[bell rings]

20:21.261 --> 20:25.098
Hi. I'm looking for Megan.

20:25.098 --> 20:28.143
Oh, the pretty blonde
with the Farrah Fawcett waves?

20:28.143 --> 20:30.103
- That's the one.
- You just missed her.

20:30.103 --> 20:33.440
But she did leave you this.

20:33.440 --> 20:36.443
[somber music]

20:36.443 --> 20:37.736
♪ ♪

20:37.736 --> 20:39.029
Okay.

20:39.029 --> 20:42.866
Well, let me know
if anything changes.

20:42.866 --> 20:44.993
Sam, hi.

20:47.913 --> 20:50.374
Wait. That was your date?

20:50.374 --> 20:52.125
[laughs]
Can you believe it?

20:52.125 --> 20:54.836
First time in my life
I'm late for anything.

20:54.836 --> 20:56.129
What happened?

20:56.129 --> 20:59.549
I got caught up.

20:59.549 --> 21:03.178
Got caught up,
or got cold feet?

21:03.178 --> 21:08.058
[laughs] Uh, we're gonna need
another round of fries.

21:08.058 --> 21:10.978
So Matteo tells us that
you're interested in robotics.

21:10.978 --> 21:13.105
Yeah, I just really love
building things.

21:13.105 --> 21:14.356
Nice.

21:14.356 --> 21:16.400
So you're a part
of a team at school?

21:16.400 --> 21:18.652
Actually, Smallville doesn't
have a robotics team.

21:18.652 --> 21:20.570
But I like to work on my
own stuff in the mornings.

21:20.570 --> 21:22.072
Oh, in the mornings?

21:22.072 --> 21:23.907
Hmm. Can you imagine?

21:23.907 --> 21:26.952
This one right here,
he likes to roll out of bed

21:26.952 --> 21:29.121
ten minutes before
it's time to leave.

21:29.121 --> 21:32.207
I'm 16. We get up late.
That's just biology.

21:32.207 --> 21:34.334
Yeah, well, you know
what beats biology?

21:34.334 --> 21:36.044
Being woken up at dawn
by roosters.

21:36.044 --> 21:37.546
[imitates rooster crowing]

21:37.546 --> 21:41.174
[laughter]

21:41.174 --> 21:42.384
Maybe we'll try that one.

21:42.384 --> 21:44.136
- [laughter]
- Okay, okay.

21:44.136 --> 21:45.762
If my dad pulls
some Old MacDonald stuff,

21:45.762 --> 21:47.806
- I'm blaming you.
- But maybe you need it.

21:47.806 --> 21:50.809
[sighs]
You know who they remind me of?

21:50.809 --> 21:52.519
[distorting]
You and me, when we were young.

21:52.519 --> 21:54.771
[clattering]

21:54.771 --> 21:55.856
Did you feel that?

21:55.856 --> 21:58.567
[clears throat, coughs]

21:58.567 --> 22:02.362
Peia, you are not well.
We should leave.

22:02.362 --> 22:04.364
I'm gonna flag the waiter
and get the check, okay?

22:04.364 --> 22:05.824
Bruno, stop.

22:05.824 --> 22:08.160
[tense music]

22:08.160 --> 22:10.954
Natalie came a long way
to have dinner with us.

22:10.954 --> 22:13.332
I'm fine.

22:13.332 --> 22:17.210
Now, Natalie, as a mother,
it is my job to tell you

22:17.210 --> 22:19.129
at least one embarrassing story
about my son.

22:19.129 --> 22:21.048
- You don't have to--
- Yeah, I do.

22:21.048 --> 22:25.260
♪ However far away ♪

22:25.260 --> 22:28.347
♪ I will always love you ♪

22:28.347 --> 22:32.017
♪ However long I stay ♪

22:32.017 --> 22:34.519
♪ I will always love you ♪

22:34.519 --> 22:37.064
See? Told you they were dope.

22:37.064 --> 22:38.565
Yeah, they're great.

22:38.565 --> 22:40.150
Pretty dark for my mom.

22:40.150 --> 22:41.401
- [laughs]
- Who is she?

22:41.401 --> 22:43.737
- [urgent knocking]
- Jordan!

22:43.737 --> 22:45.155
- [music stops]
- Hey, I heard--

22:45.155 --> 22:46.698
Yo, what the hell's
your problem?

22:46.698 --> 22:48.533
- What are you talking about?
- The fire.

22:48.533 --> 22:50.911
We didn't need Superboy flying
in there to save the day.

22:50.911 --> 22:52.746
You're pissed
because I saved someone?

22:52.746 --> 22:54.164
Dude, he was just
trying to do his job.

22:54.164 --> 22:55.957
Yeah?
Well, now I might lose mine.

22:55.957 --> 22:57.667
- Why?
- Because Jordan decided

22:57.667 --> 22:59.461
to leave that guy with me,
so now your dad thinks

22:59.461 --> 23:01.213
- I went totally rogue.
- I was just trying to help.

23:01.213 --> 23:02.839
Yeah, we didn't need
your help.

23:02.839 --> 23:04.257
Guys, stop.
Look, I'll just talk to my dad.

23:04.257 --> 23:05.384
You know you're not
the only one

23:05.384 --> 23:07.344
who has to save people, right?

23:07.344 --> 23:08.762
- I've been training for this.
- Yeah, I've been training too.

23:08.762 --> 23:10.389
That's not
the same thing at all.

23:10.389 --> 23:11.640
- Oh, why not?
- 'Cause I have heat vision,

23:11.640 --> 23:13.725
and you're taking
coffee orders!

23:13.725 --> 23:16.728
[tense music]

23:16.728 --> 23:17.896
♪ ♪

23:17.896 --> 23:20.273
Right.

23:20.273 --> 23:22.067
You're right.

23:22.067 --> 23:25.904
Guess, uh, you're the only one
that gets to be a real hero.

23:27.656 --> 23:29.699
Jon...
[door slams]

23:29.699 --> 23:31.743
[sighs]

23:39.042 --> 23:40.168
[screams]

23:40.168 --> 23:44.881
Oh, my God, flying is awesome!

23:44.881 --> 23:46.758
I mean, yeah, I do--

23:46.758 --> 23:48.802
I do feel unwell, like--

23:48.802 --> 23:50.470
like I might vomit up lunch,

23:50.470 --> 23:52.681
but if there is one thing
that I learned in college,

23:52.681 --> 23:53.723
it is how to rally.

23:53.723 --> 23:55.809
[laughs]

23:55.809 --> 23:58.562
Babe? What are you doing here?

23:58.562 --> 24:02.566
I needed more space
to go through these files.

24:02.566 --> 24:05.652
Oh, my God.

24:05.652 --> 24:08.530
This guy looks like
he was chainsawed to death.

24:08.530 --> 24:09.531
Great.

24:09.531 --> 24:11.867
I was looking for that.

24:11.867 --> 24:14.703
I thought you were done
with the Mannheim story.

24:16.788 --> 24:18.665
I know.
I'm sorry that I said that.

24:18.665 --> 24:20.542
I wasn't feeling like myself.

24:20.542 --> 24:23.044
- And Chrissy--
- You don't need to apologize.

24:23.044 --> 24:24.921
Except to our readers,
who now know

24:24.921 --> 24:27.757
way too much
about the town hall.

24:27.757 --> 24:30.469
Well, tomorrow we're running
your story about Mannheim.

24:30.469 --> 24:32.053
Are you sure?

24:32.053 --> 24:33.930
Because we just did
some more digging on Peia--

24:33.930 --> 24:37.017
And came back
with absolutely nada.

24:37.017 --> 24:38.560
I'm sure.

24:38.560 --> 24:41.188
What I said earlier
was the cancer talking.

24:41.188 --> 24:42.939
I didn't want to hurt Peia
because I know

24:42.939 --> 24:45.567
what she's going through,
but I also know

24:45.567 --> 24:47.277
that Bruno's secrets
have to be exposed,

24:47.277 --> 24:49.154
and there are a lot of them.

24:49.154 --> 24:50.655
- You found anything yet?
- No.

24:50.655 --> 24:53.325
But Clark, there is
so much stuff here on Bruno

24:53.325 --> 24:55.869
that I've never seen before.

24:55.869 --> 24:58.038
I think
this is how we nail him.

25:00.790 --> 25:03.084
What the hell
was I even thinking?

25:03.084 --> 25:05.587
Dating again,
after all this time?

25:05.587 --> 25:07.172
It's not like riding a bicycle.

25:07.172 --> 25:09.841
I'm sure it hasn't been
that long.

25:09.841 --> 25:11.468
Going on 30 years.

25:11.468 --> 25:12.469
Oh, wow.

25:12.469 --> 25:14.429
That is--huh.

25:14.429 --> 25:17.182
I have a lot of questions.
[laughs]

25:17.182 --> 25:20.143
Though they can wait
for a more appropriate time.

25:20.143 --> 25:23.355
[chuckles]

25:23.355 --> 25:25.398
After Ella left,
I just never wanted

25:25.398 --> 25:27.025
to be hurt like that again.

25:27.025 --> 25:29.945
So I buried myself in work,

25:29.945 --> 25:32.864
shut everyone out.

25:32.864 --> 25:34.950
It's not very hard
to disappear from real life

25:34.950 --> 25:37.452
when that's what you want.

25:37.452 --> 25:38.954
But wait.

25:38.954 --> 25:40.372
Why in good heavens
are you here

25:40.372 --> 25:41.790
alone on a Saturday night?

25:41.790 --> 25:43.500
Oh, I had
a bunch of work to do.

25:43.500 --> 25:46.002
And I'm trying to get rid
of these Cure tickets

25:46.002 --> 25:47.420
that I have.

25:47.420 --> 25:48.797
I'm gonna assume
that's a band

25:48.797 --> 25:51.883
and not
some weird cult situation.

25:51.883 --> 25:54.511
But why would you want
to do that?

25:54.511 --> 25:57.806
Um...
[chuckles]

25:57.806 --> 26:01.434
Because I have
no one to go with.

26:01.434 --> 26:03.937
Well, sounds like
maybe it's time

26:03.937 --> 26:06.523
for you to get
back out there too.

26:06.523 --> 26:08.525
Yeah.

26:08.525 --> 26:10.694
You're probably right.

26:10.694 --> 26:14.447
Truth is, Kyle broke my heart,

26:14.447 --> 26:17.158
and I'm terrified
of getting hurt again.

26:17.158 --> 26:20.120
[soft music]

26:20.120 --> 26:21.580
♪ ♪

26:21.580 --> 26:25.250
Wish I could tell you
it'll get easier.

26:25.250 --> 26:27.669
It won't.

26:27.669 --> 26:29.504
Not unless you take
the first step.

26:32.090 --> 26:34.759
How did you know
when you were ready?

26:34.759 --> 26:37.053
Peer pressure.

26:37.053 --> 26:39.347
Jordan insisted
I give it a try.

26:39.347 --> 26:41.474
[both laugh]

26:41.474 --> 26:43.643
Exactly.

26:43.643 --> 26:45.437
I had a responsibility
to save that guy's life

26:45.437 --> 26:47.022
that he didn't understand.

26:47.022 --> 26:48.732
It's not my fault that I have
powers and he doesn't.

26:48.732 --> 26:51.109
Yeah, but you didn't
have to rub it in his face.

26:51.109 --> 26:54.571
- That's not what I was doing.
- Jordan...

26:54.571 --> 26:57.574
just try to see it
from Jon's perspective, okay?

26:57.574 --> 26:59.784
He found something
that makes himself

26:59.784 --> 27:01.536
feel special, the same way

27:01.536 --> 27:03.163
that your powers make you
feel special,

27:03.163 --> 27:04.581
and now he might lose it.

27:04.581 --> 27:06.291
So can you just admit
that it sucks

27:06.291 --> 27:09.502
without being so defensive?

27:09.502 --> 27:11.963
You're right. It sucks.

27:11.963 --> 27:15.383
Yeah.
So maybe just go talk to him.

27:15.383 --> 27:17.010
Maybe I should.

27:17.010 --> 27:21.598
♪ ♪

27:21.598 --> 27:24.017
By the way,
going to that concert

27:24.017 --> 27:25.810
is not just about
liking the music.

27:25.810 --> 27:28.563
That's, like, the whole point
of going to a concert.

27:28.563 --> 27:30.315
Could be
that your mom's lonely

27:30.315 --> 27:34.444
and just wants to spend
some time with you.

27:34.444 --> 27:37.614
Wait, are you trying
to make me feel guilty?

27:37.614 --> 27:39.449
Yeah.

27:39.449 --> 27:41.493
[whooshes]

27:41.493 --> 27:43.620
[sighs]

27:45.080 --> 27:46.414
So let me get this straight.

27:46.414 --> 27:48.625
Bruno Mannheim
takes over Intergang

27:48.625 --> 27:50.543
after Lex Luthor kills
Boss Moxie.

27:50.543 --> 27:52.045
And most of the 86ers.

27:52.045 --> 27:53.838
With a literal chainsaw?

27:53.838 --> 27:56.091
Am I the only one
who didn't have power tools

27:56.091 --> 27:57.717
on my Lex Luthor bingo card?

27:57.717 --> 27:59.803
Luther and Moxie were
feuding over territory

27:59.803 --> 28:01.012
in South Metropolis.

28:01.012 --> 28:02.639
He wanted to send a message.

28:02.639 --> 28:04.140
Which he bragged about
on a phone line

28:04.140 --> 28:06.893
the cops happened to be
listening in on.

28:06.893 --> 28:09.104
And there are more photos.

28:09.104 --> 28:12.315
Wow, I have miraculously
not vomited yet today.

28:12.315 --> 28:15.402
Two of these guys were stabbed
with some sort of longsword.

28:15.402 --> 28:17.195
Oh, my God,
and these other two--

28:17.195 --> 28:18.780
there's barely anything left
of them.

28:18.780 --> 28:22.492
They look like they were
hit by a bus, or a...

28:22.492 --> 28:23.576
Train.

28:23.576 --> 28:25.912
[train horn blares]

28:25.912 --> 28:28.206
- No.
- It could be the same person.

28:28.206 --> 28:31.751
Let me see
the coroner's reports.

28:31.751 --> 28:33.294
Two of the 86ers were shot.

28:33.294 --> 28:35.505
Yeah, but they never found
any bullets.

28:35.505 --> 28:37.340
Where is the recording
of Luther confessing?

28:37.340 --> 28:38.675
Oh, um...

28:38.675 --> 28:41.678
[tense music]

28:41.678 --> 28:44.347
♪ ♪

28:44.347 --> 28:46.141
We need to listen
to that again.

28:48.685 --> 28:50.770
Thank you for seeing me.

28:50.770 --> 28:52.814
It's the least I could do
after you set up

28:52.814 --> 28:55.316
those security systems
for my family.

28:55.316 --> 28:56.651
My mess is the reason

28:56.651 --> 28:58.069
they needed them
in the first place.

28:58.069 --> 28:59.696
Well, not really
your mess, though.

28:59.696 --> 29:01.239
More my brother's.

29:02.949 --> 29:07.829
After seeing you, I realized

29:07.829 --> 29:10.415
how much I miss him.

29:10.415 --> 29:12.125
I felt the same way
about you.

29:14.461 --> 29:16.504
How has your daughter been?

29:16.504 --> 29:17.714
Natalie, right?

29:17.714 --> 29:20.425
Yeah. She's great.

29:20.425 --> 29:23.636
Actually, uh, Nat has
her first boyfriend,

29:23.636 --> 29:26.055
which has been kind of hard
on her dad.

29:26.055 --> 29:28.516
Oh, God, please tell me
that you have been

29:28.516 --> 29:29.684
better than our dad was.

29:29.684 --> 29:31.686
I'm working on it.

29:31.686 --> 29:34.439
[both laugh]

29:34.439 --> 29:35.899
Fortunately, he's a good kid.

29:35.899 --> 29:37.692
Lives not too far from here
in Hob's Bay.

29:37.692 --> 29:39.194
Area's really coming up
these days.

29:39.194 --> 29:40.737
That's what I hear.

29:40.737 --> 29:42.322
His family's taking her out
to a nice restaurant,

29:42.322 --> 29:44.908
this place called,
uh, Little Ace's.

29:47.410 --> 29:49.704
- You can't be serious.
- What?

29:51.164 --> 29:53.917
Little Ace's is a place
that my brother used to go to

29:53.917 --> 29:57.128
all the time
with Bruno Mannheim.

29:57.128 --> 29:59.714
♪ ♪

29:59.714 --> 30:02.801
So he only wanted
wallpaper with dinosaurs,

30:02.801 --> 30:04.928
and only dinosaurs
who were smiling.

30:04.928 --> 30:06.429
This is your first time
meeting Natalie,

30:06.429 --> 30:08.181
and this is the story
you tell her?

30:08.181 --> 30:10.600
Son, your mom has been
waiting years for this moment.

30:10.600 --> 30:12.143
Oh, Natalie.

30:12.143 --> 30:14.145
I went to every home goods
store in Metropolis,

30:14.145 --> 30:15.605
but they only had
angry dinosaurs.

30:15.605 --> 30:17.565
Oh, let me guess--too scary?

30:17.565 --> 30:19.943
- What? No.
- No, you got it.

30:19.943 --> 30:21.361
You're right!
[laughter]

30:21.361 --> 30:23.905
So I ended up having his dad

30:23.905 --> 30:27.700
draw the smiles
on the dinosaurs with a marker.

30:27.700 --> 30:30.703
Now, I am no artist,
but they looked good.

30:30.703 --> 30:32.497
- [laughter]
- They were all right. Decent.

30:32.497 --> 30:34.833
Aww.
You got your happy dinosaurs.

30:34.833 --> 30:36.209
Yeah, I did.

30:36.209 --> 30:37.585
[laughs]

30:37.585 --> 30:39.170
Welcome to Little Ace's.

30:39.170 --> 30:40.964
Oh, hey, look.
Your dad's here.

30:40.964 --> 30:47.387
♪ ♪

30:52.642 --> 30:55.603
[tense music]

30:55.603 --> 30:57.355
♪ ♪

30:57.355 --> 30:58.773
Uh, Dad?

30:58.773 --> 31:01.734
What's going on?

31:01.734 --> 31:03.736
Is this your father, Natalie?

31:03.736 --> 31:05.530
Yeah. Is everything okay?

31:08.032 --> 31:11.619
[guns cocking]

31:11.619 --> 31:15.164
Nat, we need to go.

31:17.208 --> 31:18.626
Take the kids outside.

31:18.626 --> 31:20.003
- Dad, no. Get off of me!
- Let go of me!

31:20.003 --> 31:21.129
Hey, hey, you let go--

31:21.129 --> 31:22.839
Hey, get off of me!

31:22.839 --> 31:24.757
Dad! No, let go of me!

31:24.757 --> 31:27.218
No! Bruno, don't.

31:27.218 --> 31:29.178
[grunting]

31:29.178 --> 31:30.638
Bruno, stop.

31:30.638 --> 31:33.516
[impact lands]

31:33.516 --> 31:37.645
[panting]

31:37.645 --> 31:39.355
[grunts]

31:39.355 --> 31:40.940
[groaning]

31:40.940 --> 31:42.817
Get him up.

31:42.817 --> 31:46.696
[watch beeps]

31:46.696 --> 31:50.033
I told you
if I ever saw you again,

31:50.033 --> 31:53.995
I'd show you
exactly the kind of man I am.

31:53.995 --> 31:55.747
[grunts]

31:58.041 --> 31:59.792
He had it coming.

31:59.792 --> 32:01.961
I'm not giving up
my piece of South Metropolis

32:01.961 --> 32:06.424
for Moxie or anyone else, ever.

32:06.424 --> 32:07.634
Now they won't forget it.

32:07.634 --> 32:09.135
That's him, though.

32:09.135 --> 32:10.595
That's Luther bragging
about what he did.

32:10.595 --> 32:12.972
No, no, no. It's not.
Play it again.

32:12.972 --> 32:15.058
I'm not giving up my piece
of South Metropolis

32:15.058 --> 32:16.684
for Moxie or anyone else.

32:16.684 --> 32:18.311
[buzzing]

32:18.311 --> 32:19.771
Okay, that.
That buzzing sound.

32:19.771 --> 32:21.397
Every time I faced
that sound assassin,

32:21.397 --> 32:23.191
I heard the same thing.

32:24.651 --> 32:27.946
It's an imitation
of Lex's voice.

32:27.946 --> 32:30.448
But that means
all these victims--

32:30.448 --> 32:34.994
Intergang, Boss Moxie...

32:34.994 --> 32:37.246
Lex Luthor didn't kill them.

32:37.246 --> 32:39.582
Mannheim and that assassin did.

32:42.669 --> 32:44.003
[grunts]

32:44.003 --> 32:47.548
I told you to stay away.

32:47.548 --> 32:49.759
[groans]

32:49.759 --> 32:52.512
I told you what I'd do
to your family.

32:52.512 --> 32:54.806
[grunts]

32:54.806 --> 32:57.141
Sheesh.

32:57.141 --> 32:58.351
[sighs]

32:58.351 --> 33:01.521
[suspenseful music]

33:01.521 --> 33:04.190
[whooshing]

33:04.190 --> 33:07.610
[interface beeping]

33:07.610 --> 33:09.153
And now I'm gonna do
what I should have done

33:09.153 --> 33:10.655
a long time ago.

33:10.655 --> 33:13.324
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

33:13.324 --> 33:15.576
[breathing heavily]
My daughter.

33:15.576 --> 33:17.537
You don't have
to do this, Bruno.

33:17.537 --> 33:18.955
Please.

33:18.955 --> 33:22.083
If I don't stop him,
he'll stop us.

33:22.083 --> 33:23.668
[beeping]

33:23.668 --> 33:26.504
[whirring approaching]

33:26.504 --> 33:29.215
Your suit!

33:29.215 --> 33:32.343
[high-pitched buzzing]

33:35.013 --> 33:39.142
[high-pitched warbling]
[glass shattering]

33:39.142 --> 33:40.435
What is it?

33:40.435 --> 33:41.978
John Henry.

33:44.188 --> 33:46.149
[low warbling]

33:46.149 --> 33:48.943
♪ ♪

33:48.943 --> 33:50.778
[gunfire]

33:50.778 --> 33:53.906
[high-pitched buzzing]

33:59.037 --> 34:01.706
- [crashing]
- What was that?

34:01.706 --> 34:03.249
My dad.

34:03.249 --> 34:04.625
[grunts]

34:04.625 --> 34:06.461
Come on. Come on.

34:08.796 --> 34:11.883
[high-pitched ringing]

34:15.928 --> 34:19.098
[system beeping]

34:22.435 --> 34:25.354
[grunting]

34:25.354 --> 34:28.983
♪ ♪

34:28.983 --> 34:31.069
Finish this.

34:31.069 --> 34:34.197
[high-pitched buzzing]

34:38.409 --> 34:41.788
[warped screaming]

34:44.999 --> 34:45.958
Stop!

34:45.958 --> 34:48.961
[high-pitched ringing]

34:48.961 --> 34:56.094
♪ ♪

35:00.431 --> 35:02.391
[beeping]

35:07.522 --> 35:10.608
[strained screaming]

35:15.988 --> 35:19.075
[high-pitched ringing]

35:20.618 --> 35:23.704
[heart beating rapidly]

35:26.833 --> 35:29.919
[no audible dialogue]

35:32.588 --> 35:37.218
[muffled]
Peia! No. No. No.

35:40.263 --> 35:42.056
No. No, no, no, no.

35:42.056 --> 35:44.642
[clearly]
Peia. Peia.

35:44.642 --> 35:46.936
[sobbing]

35:46.936 --> 35:48.146
Peia.

35:48.146 --> 35:49.772
Peia, come on.

35:49.772 --> 35:51.983
She needs to get
to a hospital.

35:51.983 --> 35:54.443
[somber music]

35:54.443 --> 35:57.530
I have to take her now,
or she's going to die.

35:57.530 --> 36:01.534
[sobbing]

36:01.534 --> 36:08.666
♪ ♪

36:14.380 --> 36:17.800
[breathing heavily]

36:17.800 --> 36:19.468
Dad!

36:19.468 --> 36:22.471
[distant sirens wailing]

36:22.471 --> 36:26.934
♪ ♪

36:26.934 --> 36:28.561
Leave!

36:28.561 --> 36:35.693
♪ ♪

36:45.661 --> 36:48.623
[machinery beeping]

36:48.623 --> 36:51.626
[solemn music]

36:51.626 --> 36:54.754
♪ ♪

36:54.754 --> 36:58.674
[machinery powering up]

37:02.303 --> 37:04.805
We have control.

37:04.805 --> 37:08.309
Thank you.

37:08.309 --> 37:12.939
That'll keep her powers
from working while she's here.

37:12.939 --> 37:16.400
Is that even necessary?

37:16.400 --> 37:19.111
That woman almost killed me.

37:19.111 --> 37:21.113
Not to mention all the damage
she's done in Hob's Bay.

37:21.113 --> 37:23.449
So yeah, I think
it's more than necessary.

37:26.452 --> 37:28.037
John, I know the doctors
managed to stabilize

37:28.037 --> 37:29.413
her condition,
but she still has cancer,

37:29.413 --> 37:30.665
and it's spread.

37:30.665 --> 37:32.208
She doesn't have
much time left.

37:32.208 --> 37:35.670
She's a murderer.

37:35.670 --> 37:38.047
I get that Lois may have
bonded with her

37:38.047 --> 37:40.174
during her treatments.

37:40.174 --> 37:43.010
She's a bad person.

37:43.010 --> 37:45.263
You need to remember that.

37:47.598 --> 37:48.808
I'm gonna go call Sam
so we can start

37:48.808 --> 37:50.226
figuring out our next moves.

37:50.226 --> 37:57.066
♪ ♪

37:57.358 --> 37:59.110
Sorry I have to leave
so suddenly.

37:59.110 --> 38:01.028
Is everything okay?

38:01.028 --> 38:04.282
Never a good thing
when work calls this late.

38:04.282 --> 38:06.909
Listen, I've been eating alone

38:06.909 --> 38:09.870
in places like this
for over 30 years.

38:09.870 --> 38:11.831
It's a lonely way to live.

38:11.831 --> 38:14.083
Do yourself a favor--

38:14.083 --> 38:15.501
don't be me.

38:15.501 --> 38:17.962
[soft music]

38:17.962 --> 38:21.424
Find someone to take
to that concert.

38:21.424 --> 38:23.926
Thanks, Sam.

38:28.014 --> 38:31.267
- [knock at door]
- Hey. You got a sec?

38:31.267 --> 38:33.853
Yes, sir.

38:33.853 --> 38:35.271
That's all I saw.

38:35.271 --> 38:37.273
Okay.

38:39.650 --> 38:41.319
Hey, man, look,

38:41.319 --> 38:42.945
I wasn't trying
to get you in trouble.

38:42.945 --> 38:44.655
I was just trying to help.

38:44.655 --> 38:47.658
But I really shouldn't have
said that stuff before.

38:47.658 --> 38:49.660
It doesn't matter now.

38:49.660 --> 38:51.412
Why? Did they fire you?

38:51.412 --> 38:53.706
Was that Mr. Cushing
on the phone?

38:53.706 --> 38:56.208
It was.

38:56.208 --> 38:58.044
But he hasn't made up
his mind yet.

38:58.044 --> 39:00.046
So what's the problem?

39:00.046 --> 39:03.257
He and the other firefighters
found ice inside the store.

39:03.257 --> 39:05.384
Mr. Cushing said
that this is not the first time

39:05.384 --> 39:08.888
that something like this
has happened.

39:08.888 --> 39:12.183
He thinks someone with powers
put out the fire.

39:12.183 --> 39:14.769
Congratulations, Superboy.

39:14.769 --> 39:16.979
They're on to you.

39:22.735 --> 39:25.446
[door clicks]

39:25.446 --> 39:27.490
Is Matteo's mom okay?

39:27.490 --> 39:29.283
She's contained.

39:29.283 --> 39:31.118
- Dad--
- Look.

39:31.118 --> 39:33.788
I know you didn't know
who Matteo's parents were,

39:33.788 --> 39:35.831
but you can never
see him again.

39:35.831 --> 39:37.625
Is that understood?

39:37.625 --> 39:39.418
Wait, but it's not his fault.
He didn't know either.

39:39.418 --> 39:41.128
It doesn't matter.

39:41.128 --> 39:44.590
I'm also gonna need your phone.

39:44.590 --> 39:45.925
Are you serious?

39:45.925 --> 39:47.385
Now.

39:47.385 --> 39:50.388
[tense music]

39:50.388 --> 39:57.353
♪ ♪

40:02.274 --> 40:04.151
You okay?

40:04.151 --> 40:06.487
I can't believe I was
so wrong about everything.

40:09.824 --> 40:13.911
There's no way you could
have known about Peia.

40:13.911 --> 40:16.038
That's not
who I'm talking about.

40:16.038 --> 40:18.833
You mean Lex?

40:18.833 --> 40:20.876
I think we put
Lex Luthor in prison

40:20.876 --> 40:22.837
for a crime he didn't commit.

40:22.837 --> 40:25.840
[The Cure's "Lovesong"]

40:25.840 --> 40:32.972
♪ ♪

41:31.489 --> 41:34.283
♪ However long I stay ♪

41:34.283 --> 41:38.245
♪ ♪

41:38.245 --> 41:41.582
♪ Whatever words I say ♪

41:41.582 --> 41:45.377
♪ ♪

41:45.377 --> 41:49.173
♪ I will always love you ♪

42:16.075 --> 42:19.161
Greg, move your head.
